Download the latest version of the elastic search from here - http://github.com/downloads/elasticsearch/elasticsearch-*.tar.gz


Unpack the tar file in the download directory. This should create a directory "~/Downloads/elasticsearch-*"


Pull down the elastic search service wrapper from Github.


cd ~/Downloads

git clone https://github.com/elasticsearch/elasticsearch-servicewrapper.git elasticsearch-servicewrapper
 
Now we will move the service into place


cd ~/Downloads


sudo mv elasticsearch-* /use/local/share


cd elasticsearch-servicewrapper


sudo mv service /usr/local/share/elasticsearch-*/bin


cd /usr/local/share


sudo ln -s elasticsearch-* elastic search


sudo chown -R root:wheel elasticsearch


Now start up the service


cd /usr/local/share/elasticsearch


sudo bin/service/elasticsearch start
